WEBVTT

00:00.140 --> 00:01.702
Previously on
<i>The Client List...</i>

00:01.728 --> 00:03.523
I know that you've been
seeing someone.

00:03.548 --> 00:04.377
His name is Garrett.

00:04.402 --> 00:06.354
Oh! And this is my date --
Garrett.

00:06.379 --> 00:07.862
Oh,
have we met before?

00:07.920 --> 00:10.529
You look familiar.
I get that a lot.

00:10.563 --> 00:11.830
I swear I know you.

00:11.864 --> 00:14.599
I never forget
a name or a face.

00:14.634 --> 00:15.934
I'm sure
it'll come to me.

00:15.968 --> 00:17.869
Riley, Kyle left
the country last week.

00:17.904 --> 00:20.071
He's really gone.

00:20.139 --> 00:21.907
Kyle left me and the kids
seven weeks ago,

00:21.974 --> 00:24.009
and I have no idea
if he's ever coming back.

00:24.043 --> 00:26.678
That says everything about him
and nothing about me.

00:26.712 --> 00:29.548
[ Sighs ]

00:36.789 --> 00:39.824
Catherine: You and Edgar have
broken my heart, Heathcliff.

00:39.859 --> 00:43.395
And you both come
to bewail the deed to me.

00:43.429 --> 00:46.298
Heathcliff: You teach me now
how cruel you've been --

00:46.332 --> 00:48.266
cruel and false.

00:48.301 --> 00:50.435
Why did you despise me?

00:50.503 --> 00:52.904
Why did you betray
your own heart, Cathy?

00:52.939 --> 00:55.473
I have not one word of comfort.

00:55.541 --> 00:59.277
Yes, you may kiss me and cry,
wring out my kisses and tears.

00:59.312 --> 01:00.812
You can turn over
when you're ready.

01:00.846 --> 01:03.081
Then what right had you
to leave me? What right?!

01:03.115 --> 01:05.550
Answer me -- for the poor fancy
you felt for Linton?

01:05.585 --> 01:07.385
Who's Linton?

01:07.420 --> 01:08.853
I have no clue.

01:08.888 --> 01:11.423
That's the grave
of Catherine Earnshaw.

01:11.457 --> 01:12.963
I loved her long ago
and was wretched to lose her.

01:12.964 --> 01:15.336
Is something wrong?
[ Gasps ] Oh, I don't know.

01:15.595 --> 01:16.895
Who's in there?

01:16.929 --> 01:18.663
It's supposed to be
Riley and your client,

01:18.698 --> 01:23.501
but I'm hearing
other voices.

01:23.536 --> 01:25.837
[ Chuckles ]
That's "Wuthering Heights."

01:25.871 --> 01:27.539
Josh likes to listen
to audio books

01:27.573 --> 01:28.807
during his massage.

01:28.841 --> 01:31.676
Straight man?
No extras?

01:31.744 --> 01:33.345
As a matter of fact,
yes.

01:33.379 --> 01:34.713
He's a wonderful, sensitive,
God-fearing man.

01:34.747 --> 01:36.881
Got a crush, huh?

01:36.916 --> 01:39.951
Well, we share a -- an interest
in Victorian literature.

01:39.986 --> 01:41.620
I bet it puts him
right to sleep.

01:41.654 --> 01:44.489
Yeah, pretty much.

01:46.559 --> 01:49.594
Woman: "You must not go,"
she answered.

01:49.629 --> 01:52.631
"Linton will be up immediately,"
persisted the alarmed intruder.

01:52.665 --> 01:53.598
"Edgar will not hurt us!"

01:53.633 --> 01:55.533
Who's Edgar?

01:55.568 --> 01:58.336
"I shall die. I shall die!"
Hey, now!

01:58.404 --> 02:00.805
That's...not Edgar.

02:00.840 --> 02:02.641
Oh, my gosh.
I-I'm so --

02:02.675 --> 02:03.875
I didn't realize we were doing the whole...
I didn't --

02:03.943 --> 02:05.644
I didn't --
...Rub and tug.

02:05.678 --> 02:08.013
Oh, but I did.
No. It was...good.

02:08.047 --> 02:09.648
Okay.

02:09.681 --> 02:13.118
"If he shot me so, I'd expire
with a blessing on my lips."

