02:19.584 --> 02:22.584
== sync, corrected by <font color="#00FF00">elderman</font> ==

02:22.595 --> 02:24.062
[ Breathing heavily ]

02:24.096 --> 02:25.730
I grabbed it.

02:25.765 --> 02:27.565
What?
His unit.

02:27.600 --> 02:28.800
You didn't.
I did.

02:28.834 --> 02:29.801
I took the d-train.

02:29.835 --> 02:31.670
On purpose?
No.

02:31.704 --> 02:33.705
It just kind of...happened.
I'm so sorry.

02:33.739 --> 02:36.641
Well, thanks
for covering my shift.

02:36.676 --> 02:38.943
Or uncovering it.

02:39.011 --> 02:41.880
Lacey: What do you mean,
"weird day at work"?

02:41.914 --> 02:44.282
Oh, I was
just thinking out loud.

02:44.316 --> 02:45.717
Oh,
I can't even imagine

02:45.751 --> 02:47.385
what ends up on your
massage table day after day.

02:47.420 --> 02:48.820
[ Chuckles ]
It's not always so bad.

02:48.854 --> 02:51.690
Chamomile?
Perfect.

02:51.724 --> 02:56.428
So, uh...you and Dale
were only gone three days.

02:56.462 --> 02:57.562
You know, you didn't have to
bring all that stuff back

02:57.596 --> 02:59.297
for the kids.

02:59.365 --> 03:02.746
I most certainly did.
I love spoiling them.

03:02.748 --> 03:03.802
Besides, it's good practice

03:03.827 --> 03:05.547
for when Dale and I
have a brood of our own.

03:06.806 --> 03:08.073
Oh, so it went well?

03:08.107 --> 03:10.408
Dale's back on board
for having babies?

03:10.443 --> 03:12.177
Um, yeah.

03:13.612 --> 03:14.813
Lacey Jean.

03:14.847 --> 03:17.248
He will be.

03:17.283 --> 03:18.616
He says he doesn't
want children now,

03:18.651 --> 03:20.819
but he'll feel differently
once I'm pregnant.

03:20.853 --> 03:24.756
You went off the pill
and you're not telling him.

03:24.790 --> 03:26.791
Maybe.

03:26.826 --> 03:28.593
Yes.
[ Sighs ]

03:28.661 --> 03:29.527
Lacey,
you can't do that.

03:29.595 --> 03:31.129
Maybe I can.

03:31.163 --> 03:32.564
The way I look at it,
I'm giving him what he wants

03:32.598 --> 03:33.865
before he even knows
he wants it.

03:33.899 --> 03:36.101
[ Door closes ]

03:36.135 --> 03:39.037
We are so not even done
talking about this.

03:39.071 --> 03:41.306
Linette:
Done talking about what?

03:41.340 --> 03:43.141
Girl talk.
Nothing.

03:43.175 --> 03:44.776
Well, I was gonna borrow your
carry-on, but who am I kidding?

03:44.810 --> 03:46.878
I'm packing enough clothes
for a passage to India.

03:46.912 --> 03:48.613
Okay, mama,
can you please explain to me

03:48.647 --> 03:51.783
how you going to New Orleans
with Garrett is taking it slow?

03:51.817 --> 03:53.284
I should have
never told you.

03:53.319 --> 03:54.452
Lacey: Linette,
your only resolution this year

03:54.487 --> 03:55.720
was to take things slow
with men.

03:55.755 --> 03:57.222
You two calm down.

03:57.256 --> 03:58.656
I'm not running off
and marrying him.

03:58.691 --> 03:59.758
Not yet, anyway.

04:02.828 --> 04:04.963
Can you just admit that
this trip happened suddenly?

04:04.997 --> 04:06.965
I mean, he didn't even give you
a chance to think about it.

04:06.999 --> 04:08.867
Linette:
What's to think about?

04:08.934 --> 04:13.403
I like him, he likes me,
we both like jazz.

04:14.155 --> 04:16.345
And Riley, I thought yo like him.
I do.

04:16.409 --> 04:18.834
Good. You haven't said that
since three husbands ago.

04:18.845 --> 04:20.745
I'm just worried that you don't
know him very well. That's all.

04:20.781 --> 04:22.014
Honey, do not.

04:22.048 --> 04:23.783
Do not what?

04:23.817 --> 04:26.245
Hint that I'm making a mistake.
I've made plenty of them.

04:26.345 --> 04:27.912
And I've learned that
you can't find out about love

04:27.947 --> 04:30.114
unless you fling yourself
out there.

04:30.182 --> 04:31.249
Oh, you have definitely
flung it.

04:31.283 --> 04:33.017
Amen.

04:33.085 --> 04:35.820
Now, I understand why
you'd be gun-shy about men.

04:35.854 --> 04:37.522
Considering.

04:37.556 --> 04:39.257
Mama,
this is not about me.

04:39.325 --> 04:41.259
It wasn't,
but now it is.

04:41.293 --> 04:43.394
You took off your wedding ring.
That's a start.

04:43.429 --> 04:45.163
Actually,
it felt more like an end.

04:45.230 --> 04:46.598
I know it's been hard
with this Kyle business,

04:46.665 --> 04:47.932
but you can't just give up

04:47.967 --> 04:49.534
because you had
one bad experience.

04:49.568 --> 04:51.102
Mama, it's been
my only experience.

04:51.136 --> 04:52.470
You should date.
Have some fun.

04:52.504 --> 04:54.939
I don't --
Yeah!

04:54.974 --> 04:56.941
I don't...
fling it like you do.

04:56.976 --> 04:59.911
Well, sometimes when you
take a chance, it pays off big.

04:59.945 --> 05:02.547
Now, would you please
let me have some fun?

05:02.581 --> 05:04.248
Somebody around here's
got to.

05:06.619 --> 05:08.353
I'm fun.

05:08.387 --> 05:11.422
So am I.

05:11.457 --> 05:15.360
Evan: Well,
how long is that gonna take?

05:15.427 --> 05:16.928
All right.

05:16.962 --> 05:19.564
Well, just let me know
when it's gonna be done.

05:19.632 --> 05:23.067
All right. Thanks.

05:23.102 --> 05:25.737
Unbelievable. Now they say
it's the alternator.

05:25.771 --> 05:26.971
And this
better be a mistake,

05:27.039 --> 05:28.439
'cause Garza promised me
that raise.

05:28.474 --> 05:30.141
Okay, well,
maybe they screwed it up,

05:30.175 --> 05:31.943
but you won't know
unless you ask him.

05:31.977 --> 05:34.479
Look, you need this job,
and I know what that feels like.

05:34.513 --> 05:36.614
Just kill him with kindness.
It works for me.

05:36.649 --> 05:38.282
Yeah, it would be easier
just to kill him.

05:38.317 --> 05:40.885
Oh, no. You're too
pretty to be in prison.

05:40.919 --> 05:43.588
[ Laughs ]

05:43.622 --> 05:45.523
I'll get a ride
later tonight.

05:45.557 --> 05:47.692
No way. Come on. I'm used to
driving the kids around.

05:47.726 --> 05:50.828
You didn't even throw food or
sing "Party in the U.S.A." once.

05:50.863 --> 05:52.330
Maybe next time.

05:52.364 --> 05:54.399
Bye.

05:54.466 --> 05:56.434
Ooh, Evan!

05:56.468 --> 06:00.338
Evan!

06:00.406 --> 06:02.473
Hey, what you doing later,
baby, huh?

06:02.508 --> 06:04.776
Calling your wife, Joe,
and you should know better.

06:04.810 --> 06:06.377
Ooh!

06:06.412 --> 06:07.845
[ Laughs ]
[ Laughs ]

06:07.880 --> 06:10.348
Ow!

06:10.382 --> 06:13.451
Hey.

06:21.493 --> 06:24.395
[ Indistinct conversations ]

06:24.430 --> 06:25.730
We heard.

06:25.764 --> 06:26.964
[ Groans ]
I know.

06:26.999 --> 06:28.466
It happened.
I was in the zone.

06:28.500 --> 06:30.935
Before you know it,
I was in his zone.

06:31.003 --> 06:32.637
Well, that's a first --
although, I can't blame you.

06:32.705 --> 06:34.505
The guy is gorgeous.

06:34.540 --> 06:37.909
Josh is a kind soul,
if you have any designs on him.

06:37.943 --> 06:39.811
What are you talking about?
She's talking about dating.

06:39.878 --> 06:42.947
You should try it. It's exciting.
Yeah, so is sky-diving,

06:42.981 --> 06:44.348
but I don't want to do that,
either.

06:44.383 --> 06:45.950
Honey, why are you
holding back?

06:45.984 --> 06:47.351
Well, for starters,
I'm married.

06:47.386 --> 06:49.921
I'm a mom, and I haven't
been on a date since...

06:49.955 --> 06:52.623
I have not been on a date
since the 20th century.

06:52.658 --> 06:54.125
Hilarious, Dee Ann.

06:54.193 --> 06:56.461
Riley, what do you mean
you haven't been on a date --

06:56.528 --> 06:58.096
Since Kyle.

06:58.163 --> 06:59.363
We met in high school,
and five dates later,

06:59.398 --> 07:01.365
we were shopping
for baby furniture.

07:01.400 --> 07:03.601
Oh, my gosh.
Kyle was your first?

07:03.635 --> 07:06.237
My only.

07:06.271 --> 07:11.409
I had no idea.

07:11.443 --> 07:13.678
Dee Ann: Lord, you got to
get back out there sometime.

07:13.712 --> 07:15.346
Honey,
start living your life.

07:15.380 --> 07:16.981
Speaking of, Duke is
out of town this weekend.

07:17.015 --> 07:18.649
We should all go out
this Friday night.

07:18.684 --> 07:23.855
I can't.
I have plans.

07:23.889 --> 07:24.922
[ Chuckles ]
[ Cellphone rings ]

07:24.957 --> 07:25.957
Hello?

07:31.730 --> 07:32.897
She's got
something going on.

07:32.931 --> 07:34.565
Early this morning,
I saw her texting.

07:34.600 --> 07:38.469
I asked her about it. She almost
jumped out of her skin.

07:38.504 --> 07:39.670
Secret boyfriend?

07:39.705 --> 07:41.205
Secret something.

07:44.009 --> 07:46.978
[ Indistinct conversations ]

07:47.045 --> 07:48.379
I need that drywall
finished today.

07:48.413 --> 07:51.362
[ Speaks Spanish ]
No more excuses.

07:52.257 --> 07:53.720
Wash got the wrong materials

07:53.892 --> 07:54.683
You got a minute?

07:54.924 --> 07:56.391
Yeah.

07:55.487 --> 07:58.055
I'm, uh -- I'm assuming
this is a mistake.

07:58.090 --> 08:00.691
You said my -- my raise
would start this paycheck.

08:00.726 --> 08:02.860
Did I?
Maybe you misunderstood.

08:02.895 --> 08:04.462
I didn't misunderstand.

08:04.496 --> 08:06.531
I've been doing
foreman's work for months

08:06.565 --> 08:08.499
on the promise
that I'd get paid for it.

08:08.567 --> 08:10.568
Listen, we've lost
three bids this month,

08:10.602 --> 08:12.570
and corporate
is pushing for more layoffs.

08:12.604 --> 08:13.938
Well,
I've seen the books.

08:13.972 --> 08:15.006
I mean, we're turning
a profit on every job.

08:15.040 --> 08:16.741
[ Chuckles ]

08:16.775 --> 08:19.277
You're not seeing
the big picture here, huh?

08:19.311 --> 08:20.678
Look, I'm getting squeezed
from the top,

08:20.746 --> 08:23.681
but I'll, uh...
I'll see what I can do.

08:23.715 --> 08:25.883
I appreciate it.

08:25.918 --> 08:27.952
Hold on a second.

08:27.986 --> 08:30.421
I hadn't seen your sister-in-law
since Kyle left.

08:30.489 --> 08:35.393
How's she doing?

08:35.460 --> 08:37.428
Uh-huh.

08:37.462 --> 08:38.895
And, um,
since he's gone, uh...

08:38.931 --> 08:40.898
Are you tapping that?

08:40.966 --> 08:41.899
[ Chuckles ]

08:41.933 --> 08:49.407
Excuse me?
Riley.

08:49.441 --> 08:50.975
But speaking for myself,

08:51.009 --> 08:53.010
I wouldn't let a woman
like that get by,

08:53.045 --> 08:55.112
even if she was
my brother's wife.

08:58.984 --> 09:01.085
[ Indistinct conversations ]

09:06.558 --> 09:08.826
Riley.

09:08.861 --> 09:10.394
Should I just start with,
"I'm mortified," don't.

09:10.429 --> 09:12.196
Don't even --
and then apologize, or should I apologize

09:12.264 --> 09:13.464
you don't have to do this.
And then just let it spiral down from there?

09:13.498 --> 09:15.499
No, look. It was memorable.
Unique.

09:15.534 --> 09:17.902
And not at all
what I was going for.

09:17.936 --> 09:20.037
I know. I know.

09:20.072 --> 09:22.206
Look, I may have left my wallet here.
Oh, right.

09:22.274 --> 09:23.975
I mean, you did leave
kind of fast.

09:24.009 --> 09:26.177
I'm surprised
you remembered your pants.

09:26.211 --> 09:27.812
Yeah, they kind of, uh,
slowed me down

09:27.846 --> 09:29.180
in the sprint to the car.

09:29.214 --> 09:30.481
I'll just see
if Georgia has your wallet.

09:30.515 --> 09:32.516
All right. Thanks.
Hey, uh...

09:32.551 --> 09:34.352
What are you doing on --
on Saturday?

09:34.386 --> 09:35.753
Well, I don't usually
work the weekends,

09:35.787 --> 09:37.288
but let me see.

09:37.322 --> 09:38.923
No, no, no.
I meant, uh, like a date.

09:38.957 --> 09:40.825
Saturday night.

09:42.728 --> 09:44.562
Or -- or coffee.

09:44.596 --> 09:46.631
Or desserts.

09:46.698 --> 09:48.266
Drinks.

09:48.300 --> 09:51.235
I mean, to be honest,
I don't really care what we do,

09:51.270 --> 09:54.171
but I think it may be fun
to spend some time together.

09:54.206 --> 09:56.374
You know,
with my clothes on.

09:56.408 --> 10:04.081
[ Chuckles ]
I don't -- I don't know.

10:04.116 --> 10:06.550
A little.

10:06.618 --> 10:08.352
Embarrassing
and humiliating.

10:11.890 --> 10:13.624
[ Laughs ]
So...

10:14.973 --> 10:16.240
What do you say?

10:26.120 --> 10:27.871
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
That's it?

10:27.872 --> 10:28.972
That's what
you told Josh?

10:29.040 --> 10:31.474
That, and I'd
think about it.

10:31.542 --> 10:32.509
If I were you,
I'd just play "get."

10:32.543 --> 10:35.478
I don't know
if I'm ready.

10:35.513 --> 10:36.646
Of all the ways
that you're ready.

10:36.714 --> 10:38.448
But, I mean,
husband gone, ring off.

10:38.482 --> 10:40.250
But that's really negative.
I'm all about positivity.

10:40.284 --> 10:41.685
The only way to tell
if you're ready

10:41.752 --> 10:43.086
is to go out on a date
and see if you're ready.

10:43.120 --> 10:45.021
That didn't make any sense.

10:45.056 --> 10:47.057
Well, neither does saying no
to someone like Josh Harper.

10:47.124 --> 10:48.692
You won't hear me say this
often, but Dee Ann's right.

10:48.726 --> 10:50.527
If there's any guy
worth giving a shot, he's it.

10:50.561 --> 10:52.262
[ Cellphone rings ]

10:52.296 --> 10:55.165
Ooh. [ Gasps ]
Hello, mystery man!

10:55.199 --> 10:56.399
Dang it, Dee Ann!

10:56.434 --> 10:58.134
Sam says,
"looking forward to it."

10:58.169 --> 11:00.270
I knew it! It is none of your business!
Look, if she wanted us to know,

11:00.304 --> 11:01.638
she'd tell us.
Thank you, Riley.

11:01.672 --> 11:04.374
She won't give anything up,
and it's driving me crazy.

11:04.442 --> 11:06.142
You know why I don't tell you
about my life?

11:06.177 --> 11:07.477
'Cause y'all are a bunch of
jackals when it comes to gossip.

11:07.545 --> 11:09.879
Not me.
Okay. I got to go.

11:09.914 --> 11:11.481
Yes, you are.
[ Scoffs ]

11:11.549 --> 11:13.316
Okay.
Thank you.

11:13.350 --> 11:14.984
Hey, honey, I've been
meaning to ask you --

11:15.019 --> 11:16.986
how's your mom and
her boyfriend doing these days?

11:17.021 --> 11:18.321
[ Scoffs ]
Oh, hot and heavy.

11:18.355 --> 11:19.789
Did you remember
where you knew him from?

11:19.824 --> 11:21.725
Oh, for the life of me,
I can't place him.

11:21.759 --> 11:23.860
Mr. Landry wasn't
on the client list, was he?

11:23.928 --> 11:25.328
Well, now,
that I would remember.

11:25.362 --> 11:28.064
Okay.

11:28.099 --> 11:30.033
Landry?

11:30.067 --> 11:33.470
Missed a spot.

11:35.206 --> 11:36.673
Oh, people like me
are annoying.

11:36.707 --> 11:38.508
[ Laughs ]
Well, you're forgiven.

11:38.542 --> 11:40.443
Linette told me that you're
taking her to New Orleans.

11:40.478 --> 11:42.145
Oh, yeah, yeah.

11:42.179 --> 11:43.847
No, I've never been aboard
the Sunset Limited.

11:43.881 --> 11:47.250
Oh, it's very
Rhett Butler of you.

11:47.284 --> 11:49.419
Ashley Wilkes,
actually.

11:49.453 --> 11:51.488
Ashley Wilkes
was a true gentleman,

11:51.522 --> 11:54.190
not a scoundrel
like Rhett.

11:54.225 --> 11:56.159
Thank you, ma'am.

11:56.193 --> 11:59.996
Oh, I hope you didn't
want to take me to lunch.

12:00.030 --> 12:01.631
I just wanted to ask you
in person

12:01.699 --> 12:04.100
if it would be okay if we don't
stay in the French Quarter?

12:04.135 --> 12:06.202
Oh, no! Why not?
So romantic.

12:06.237 --> 12:09.038
I-I mean, I think so.

12:09.106 --> 12:11.808
I think
you missed a spot.

12:11.842 --> 12:13.276
That it's gonna be
clear skies and a full moon

12:13.310 --> 12:14.677
when we're there,
and I just thought

12:14.712 --> 12:16.579
it might be
a little more romantic

12:16.647 --> 12:19.215
if we had a nighttime view
of the Mississippi

12:19.250 --> 12:20.984
from our room.

12:21.018 --> 12:21.985
Huh?

12:22.052 --> 12:23.486
Whatever you like.

12:23.521 --> 12:26.022
You've planned
such a marvelous trip already.

12:26.056 --> 12:28.291
All right.
I'll see you later.

12:28.359 --> 12:29.392
[ Laughing ]

12:30.961 --> 12:33.897
Oh. Go on.
Shoo, now.

12:33.964 --> 12:35.365
I've got clients
with all sorts of issues --

12:35.432 --> 12:38.434
some even
have to do with hair.

12:42.540 --> 12:45.175
You see what's happening here,
don't you?

12:45.209 --> 12:47.010
It's written
all over his face.

12:47.077 --> 12:48.178
What's that,
Miss Lacey?

12:48.212 --> 12:49.546
I don't have
my reading glasses.

12:49.580 --> 13:00.390
Oh, Linette, come on.
He's smitten.

13:00.424 --> 13:01.958
You're both cuckoo.

13:01.992 --> 13:04.060
Look, I don't know
what Riley thinks,

13:04.094 --> 13:06.629
but I am telling you.

13:06.664 --> 13:08.031
Well, I've been
proposed to enough

13:08.065 --> 13:09.599
that I can see it coming
from a country mile.

13:09.633 --> 13:14.404
A few times, I actually
managed to get out of the way.

13:14.438 --> 13:16.539
Garrett is acting
a little funny.

13:16.574 --> 13:19.075
Maybe he does have
something on his mind.

13:19.109 --> 13:22.145
I've been so busy having
a good time, I didn't notice.

13:22.213 --> 13:24.514
Maybe that's what we mean
when we say "love is blind."

13:25.749 --> 13:28.351
Oh!
Mrs. Peck is ready.

13:28.419 --> 13:31.387
And what about you?

13:31.422 --> 13:36.392
Ready? To get married?
Oh, I was born ready.

13:36.427 --> 13:40.029
When it comes to Garrett Landry,
oh, yes, indeedy.

13:47.738 --> 13:51.374
Look what Mr. straight massage
sent you today.

13:51.408 --> 13:53.142
It was at the front desk.

13:53.210 --> 13:56.579
It's one of those pre-paid
disposable phones.

13:56.614 --> 13:59.616
With just
his name and number in it.

13:59.650 --> 14:02.085
I think it's wildly romantic.
[ Chuckles ]

14:02.119 --> 14:05.755
It is cute, is what it is.
Too cute!

14:05.789 --> 14:07.590
I'm about to leave Bobby
for this guy. [ Laughs ]

14:07.658 --> 14:09.025
Girl,
what's it gonna take?

14:09.093 --> 14:11.661
[ Laughs ]

14:11.695 --> 14:13.129
[ Sighs ]

14:13.163 --> 14:14.264
[ Beep ]

14:14.298 --> 14:15.732
[ Ringing ]

14:15.766 --> 14:17.667
[ Cellphone rings ]
Uh, hello?

14:17.701 --> 14:21.475
Hi, it's Riley.
Hey,hey Riley. What's going on?

14:22.239 --> 14:25.341
Hey, Carlos!
Very nice on the dishes there.

14:25.409 --> 14:27.277
Just -- just get --
I need the ribs, okay?

14:27.311 --> 14:30.446
Thanks, man. Uh, sorry.
It's -- it's nuts here.

14:30.481 --> 14:32.448
Uh, so, you got my gift,
I guess.

14:32.483 --> 14:34.984
I did.
I'm using it right now.

14:35.019 --> 14:37.153
So, h-how are you?

14:37.187 --> 14:38.788
I'm good.

14:38.822 --> 14:42.659
I was just thinking about how
awful our first encounter was.

14:42.693 --> 14:46.095
Um...Okay.

14:46.130 --> 14:47.964
That it probably
couldn't get much worse.

14:47.998 --> 14:50.533
So, I'm --
I'm gonna take that as a yes.

14:52.536 --> 14:54.103
It's a yes.

15:02.085 --> 15:04.953
[ Cellphone rings ]
Give me a second.

15:04.988 --> 15:07.556
Riley, hey. What's up?
Riley: Hey, I'm so sorry.

15:07.590 --> 15:08.993
I can't get there in time.

15:09.018 --> 15:10.698
That's all right. I'll just get
a ride with one of the guys.

15:11.161 --> 15:12.728
You sure?
Yeah.

15:12.796 --> 15:14.897
I mean, you can't be chauffeuring
my ass around forever.

15:14.931 --> 15:17.266
Everything okay?
Uh, yes.

15:17.300 --> 15:20.002
As a matter of fact,
everything's really good.

15:20.036 --> 15:22.538
Fantastic. You gonna tell me
what's making you so happy?

15:22.572 --> 15:28.010
Oh, uh...

15:28.044 --> 15:30.512
It's nothing. Thank you so much
for understanding.

15:30.547 --> 15:32.080
Bye.
[ Beep ]

15:32.115 --> 15:36.084
[ Indistinct shouting ]

15:46.129 --> 15:48.130
Very clever.

15:48.164 --> 15:50.432
Oh, look, I didn't care
if it was clever.

15:50.466 --> 15:51.967
I just cared
if it worked.

15:52.035 --> 15:54.069
Well,
looks like it did.

15:54.103 --> 15:55.904
So, uh,
you want to go in?

15:55.939 --> 15:57.005
I think
you'll like the place.

15:57.040 --> 15:59.074
[ Sighs ]
Sure.

15:59.108 --> 16:00.976
In a minute.

16:01.010 --> 16:03.512
You know, one of my
favorite things about Texas --

16:03.517 --> 16:04.160
Big sky.

16:04.185 --> 16:06.185
I was just gonna say that!
You beat me to the punch.

16:06.249 --> 16:10.018
Yeah.
Yeah. Big sky.

16:10.053 --> 16:11.286
[ Sighs ]

16:11.321 --> 16:12.788
I've been running around
so much lately.

16:12.822 --> 16:15.190
I haven't even had a chance
to just look up

16:15.225 --> 16:17.960
and see where I'm going
or where I've been.

16:21.197 --> 16:23.465
What?

16:23.499 --> 16:28.237
Nothing. I'm just
very glad you made it.

16:30.940 --> 16:33.575
[ Sighs ] So...

16:33.643 --> 16:35.444
When does the date
officially start?

16:35.478 --> 16:39.248
Officially?
Uh...Let me see.

16:39.282 --> 16:44.186
Oh, maybe once you, uh,
sit down, place your order.

16:44.220 --> 16:46.054
Talk about your childhood.
Parents and siblings.

16:46.089 --> 16:47.556
Hopes and dreams.

16:47.590 --> 16:50.158
I mean, wow. We really
have a lot ahead of us.

16:50.193 --> 16:52.261
A lot of stuff.
[ Laughs ]

16:54.330 --> 16:57.900
So, are you up for it?
The official start time?

16:57.934 --> 17:00.502
Yeah.

17:00.570 --> 17:01.470
Yeah, I think I am.

17:06.209 --> 17:09.144
Or maybe just we could do
a little...

17:09.212 --> 17:11.480
More sky?

17:11.513 --> 17:15.817
Yeah. Exactly.

17:20.189 --> 17:21.890
Georgia: Yes, I know.

17:21.925 --> 17:25.127
I know, but please.
It does make a difference.

17:25.161 --> 17:29.331
His name is Garrett Landry,
not Landry Garrett.

17:29.365 --> 17:31.967
[ Knock on door ]
It's open!

17:32.035 --> 17:36.038
Ma'am, I've never heard
of Landry Garrett.

17:36.072 --> 17:37.639
What can I do you for,
baby?

17:37.674 --> 17:38.640
I'll wait
till you finish.

17:38.675 --> 17:41.109
No, honey,
don't say that.

17:41.144 --> 17:42.411
No, no, no.
Listen, I am still here.

17:42.445 --> 17:43.612
I may be on this phone
all night.

17:43.680 --> 17:47.549
I need to take
tomorrow evening off.

17:47.583 --> 17:49.451
Jolene, you can hardly
make ends meet as it is.

17:49.485 --> 17:50.686
Uh, no, no, no.

17:50.720 --> 17:55.557
No, no!
Do not put me on hold.

17:55.591 --> 17:58.327
I wouldn't ask
if it wasn't real important.

17:58.394 --> 18:00.429
Honey, you know I will support
you as much as I can,

18:00.463 --> 18:02.264
but now when it gets
to where I can't count on you,

18:03.533 --> 18:05.200
Thank you.

18:05.234 --> 18:07.536
Jolene.

18:07.570 --> 18:10.072
Arrested?
On what charge?

18:10.106 --> 18:11.540
No, no, no.

18:11.574 --> 18:13.742
I've got all the time
in the world for this.

18:13.776 --> 18:17.045
So, no, no, just, uh --
just the two dogs

18:17.080 --> 18:24.052
and, um, the meanest siamese
on the planet.

18:24.087 --> 18:25.654
Just by staring at it
really hard.

18:25.688 --> 18:27.456
Wow. That is
one powerful cat.

18:27.490 --> 18:28.991
Yeah,
she's frightening.

18:29.025 --> 18:31.326
Anyway, your turn.

18:31.361 --> 18:34.696
Oh, well, um...

18:34.731 --> 18:36.999
No dogs.
No dogs.

18:37.033 --> 18:39.735
Two kids.
Two --

18:39.769 --> 18:43.005
Oh, so, you, uh, you saved
the best for last, didn't you?

18:43.039 --> 18:44.906
Travis is 7
and a nut-ball,

18:44.941 --> 18:48.110
and, uh,
Katie is 5 going on 25.

18:48.144 --> 18:49.411
Wow.
I love kids.

18:49.445 --> 18:51.380
I, um -- I have a niece
and a nephew.

18:51.414 --> 18:53.115
I-I coach
their soccer team.

18:53.182 --> 18:56.618
Wow. You are a complete
surprise, Josh Harper.

18:56.652 --> 18:58.854
I thought the kid thing
was just gonna do you right in.

18:58.888 --> 19:00.222
[ Chuckles ]
No, not at all. Not at all.

19:00.289 --> 19:01.590
You know
what almost got me

19:01.624 --> 19:03.125
was the chicken story
from your childhood.

19:03.192 --> 19:04.559
[ Laughs ] I mean,
that was a little bizarre.

19:04.594 --> 19:06.228
Well, I raised them
and ate them.

19:06.262 --> 19:07.963
You know,
it's the cycle of life.

19:07.997 --> 19:09.898
[ Laughs ]
[ Laughs ]

19:09.932 --> 19:13.535
[ Sighs ]
You are one tough broad.

19:13.603 --> 19:16.171
Well, you have to be, you know,
to get through a whole day.

19:16.205 --> 19:17.239
Single mom, all that work.

19:17.273 --> 19:18.173
Yeah.

19:20.276 --> 19:22.144
Hmm.

19:22.211 --> 19:23.678
Let's -- let's talk
about your job.

19:23.713 --> 19:25.013
[ Laughs ]

19:25.048 --> 19:27.749
[ Laughs ]
What do you mean?

19:27.784 --> 19:31.086
I'm not naive. I know what --
what goes on there.

19:31.120 --> 19:34.556
You know,
I ran out the other day.

19:34.624 --> 19:39.261
You and all the other girls had
a field day with what happened.

19:39.328 --> 19:41.463
[ Chuckles ]
Yes, we did.

19:41.531 --> 19:42.898
Yeah,
a little play-by-play

19:42.932 --> 19:44.399
of all your weirdest
sessions on the table.

19:44.467 --> 19:46.168
[ Laughs ]
Yeah.

19:46.202 --> 19:48.336
This one's definitely gonna
go down as a hall of famer.

19:48.371 --> 19:49.371
Brutal. Brutal.

19:49.405 --> 19:51.406
Just for the record,

19:51.474 --> 19:54.109
that is the fastest anyone has
ever run away from me before.

19:54.143 --> 19:56.711
It was great for my ego.
[ Laughs ]

19:56.746 --> 19:59.281
Sorry.
Yeah.

19:59.315 --> 20:04.319
We should, uh -- we should
do this again sometime.

20:04.353 --> 20:06.121
You should, you know,
get a sitter,

20:06.155 --> 20:07.489
I don't know,
next Saturday night.

20:07.557 --> 20:09.658
Or do the kids
stay with their dad?

20:09.692 --> 20:11.726
Nope. Their dad is, uh,
not in the picture.

20:11.761 --> 20:14.296
He left us
a few months ago.

20:14.330 --> 20:16.098
Just...left.

20:17.767 --> 20:22.404
A few, uh --
a few months ago.

20:22.472 --> 20:25.140
Wow. So, you don't --
you don't know where he is?

20:25.174 --> 20:29.744
No, or if we'll ever
see him again.

20:29.779 --> 20:31.446
But, I mean,
he -- he could --

20:31.481 --> 20:34.116
[ chuckles ]
He could come back.

20:34.183 --> 20:36.418
Like, at anytime.

20:45.394 --> 20:46.428
[ Sighs ]

20:58.074 --> 20:59.574
[ Sighs ]

20:59.609 --> 21:01.209
These flowers
are beautiful.

21:01.244 --> 21:02.978
Yeah, I had no idea
what your favorite flower was,

21:03.012 --> 21:05.814
but I-I know
Linette likes these, so...

21:05.848 --> 21:07.716
Stargazer lilies.
Like mother, like daughter.

21:07.783 --> 21:09.885
So, it is a surprise,
you just coming by.

21:09.952 --> 21:11.753
Well, and I'm glad
that I caught you at home.

21:11.787 --> 21:13.088
Okay,
so what's all this about?

21:13.122 --> 21:14.623
Well, it's about
my wanting to do

21:14.657 --> 21:16.224
what's right
by your mama.

21:16.259 --> 21:24.766
Okay.

21:24.800 --> 21:27.135
I want to marry Linette.

21:27.203 --> 21:29.738
This weekend?

21:29.805 --> 21:32.841
Well, soon,
but I would like your blessing.

21:32.875 --> 21:34.142
I don't understand
what the rush is.

21:34.210 --> 21:35.844
No, there's no rush.

21:35.878 --> 21:39.181
But it's just that at my age,
when you know, you know.

21:39.215 --> 21:43.018
And when I met your mom,
believe me, I knew.

21:43.052 --> 21:45.253
Okay, but my mama,
she dives in head first.

21:45.321 --> 21:48.690
Always has, and...
that concerns me.

21:48.724 --> 21:50.225
And you're
looking out for her,

21:50.259 --> 21:51.927
and I respect that, Riley.
So you want my approval.

21:51.994 --> 21:54.729
Well, I'm just
an old-fashioned kind of guy.

21:54.764 --> 21:56.398
And if I could
go to her father and ask...

21:56.432 --> 21:58.033
Right.

21:58.067 --> 21:59.634
Well, and I don't really think
it'd be wise for me

21:59.669 --> 22:01.303
to go to her ex-husbands.

22:01.370 --> 22:04.873
I understand two of them
are big into deer hunting.

22:04.907 --> 22:09.477
[ Chuckling ] Yeah.
I would steer clear of them.

22:11.480 --> 22:13.815
Do you love her?

22:16.419 --> 22:18.653
Very much.

22:20.723 --> 22:23.058
[ Sighs ]

22:23.125 --> 22:26.394
Look,
the thing is...

22:26.429 --> 22:28.330
I don't know
if I'm okay with this.

22:28.364 --> 22:29.397
[ Sighs ]

22:29.432 --> 22:31.833
But it's not
my decision to make.

22:33.736 --> 22:38.073
But if you ever hurt her
or upset her...

22:38.107 --> 22:40.075
Believe me -- I'd be crazy
to mess with you two.

22:40.109 --> 22:41.676
You are a pair
to be reckoned with.

22:41.711 --> 22:43.411
As long as
we're clear.

22:43.446 --> 22:45.313
Okay.

22:45.348 --> 22:47.649
Do you think that we could
just keep this between us?

22:47.717 --> 22:49.517
Because I'd kind of like to
surprise her.

22:58.160 --> 23:01.062
[ Sighs ]

23:02.732 --> 23:05.433
Lacey: Riley?
[ Sighs ]

23:05.468 --> 23:08.336
Riley? Riley,
are you back there?

23:08.371 --> 23:10.538
Yeah. I am.

23:10.606 --> 23:12.807
Hey.

23:12.842 --> 23:14.776
What on earth
was Garrett doing here?

23:14.844 --> 23:16.177
I just saw him
walking out.

23:17.480 --> 23:19.281
[ Gasps ] Oh, my God.
He's gonna ask her.

23:19.315 --> 23:21.049
He's gonna ask Linette
to marry him.

23:21.083 --> 23:22.783
Yeah. Can you believe that?
And he wanted my blessing.

23:22.808 --> 23:23.918
Aww.

23:23.919 --> 23:26.488
I think
it's wildly romantic.

23:26.522 --> 23:28.790
Yeah, romantic, lunatic --
one of the two.

23:28.824 --> 23:30.859
Man, I got to stop
doing that.

23:30.893 --> 23:33.895
You know what? I got to stop
worrying about everybody else.

23:33.929 --> 23:36.898
Oh. That's new.
It's new Riley.

23:36.932 --> 23:39.434
Yeah, 'cause he's either gonna
propose this weekend or not.

23:39.468 --> 23:40.969
You know,
or maybe they'll elope.

23:41.003 --> 23:42.971
Or it could just be
a 300-person shindig

23:43.005 --> 23:44.673
at the Colvin Mansion --
I don't even know.

23:44.707 --> 23:47.509
Uh, could you please
bring back new Riley?

23:47.576 --> 23:48.743
I was just
starting to like her.

23:48.778 --> 23:50.879
Sorry. I'm trying.

23:50.946 --> 23:52.681
Look, right now
what I want to know

23:52.748 --> 23:54.849
is if you ever
came clean with Dale.

23:54.884 --> 23:57.352
Not quite. And he's starting to
suspect something.

23:57.420 --> 23:59.321
He's begged off sex
for days.

23:59.355 --> 24:00.989
And I keep losing out
to the Astros.

24:01.023 --> 24:03.525
I don't think you're
looking at this realistically.

24:03.559 --> 24:06.227
Having kids is not
all sunshine and puppy dogs.

24:06.262 --> 24:08.129
Great.
You sound just like him.

24:08.197 --> 24:10.198
Well,
it's true, you know.

24:10.266 --> 24:12.667
It's -- it's strep throat
and trips to the E.R.

24:12.702 --> 24:14.369
Thomas the Tank Engine.

24:14.403 --> 24:16.671
Let me tell you something
about Thomas the Tank Engine.

24:16.706 --> 24:18.807
Never stops singing.

24:18.841 --> 24:21.276
And you wouldn't change it
for the world.

24:21.310 --> 24:22.844
True.

24:25.081 --> 24:26.848
Riley, I know
that you don't approve

24:26.882 --> 24:28.917
of how
I'm going about this.

24:28.951 --> 24:31.319
But I am doing it
for all the right reasons.

24:31.354 --> 24:34.356
All the wrong ways.

24:34.390 --> 24:36.691
Come on.

24:36.726 --> 24:38.360
[ Sighs ]
Necklace.

24:38.394 --> 24:41.996
Come on!
Thank you.

24:42.031 --> 24:44.132
What, were you on a date
or something?

24:44.166 --> 24:47.168
[ Gasps ] You were!
You were on a date!

24:47.203 --> 24:49.170
I totally did.
I totally went on a date.

24:49.238 --> 24:51.606
Oh, shut up!
How could you not tell me?

24:51.640 --> 24:53.541
Okay, well,
he's tall, dark, and handsome.

24:53.576 --> 24:55.176
Nice, honest.

24:55.211 --> 24:56.277
Yuck.

24:56.312 --> 24:58.480
It's never gonna work out.
Ah.

24:58.514 --> 25:00.815
That's why you want to
keep the focus off of you.

25:00.850 --> 25:03.418
Keeping busy
has its advantages.

25:03.486 --> 25:06.154
So, who is he? Are you
trying to keep it a secret?

25:06.188 --> 25:08.656
God, it's like
you're living a double life.

25:08.724 --> 25:10.158
Linette:
Riley, we're home.

25:10.192 --> 25:11.726
Travis: Hey, mom!
Katie: Mom, we're home!

25:11.794 --> 25:14.829
You know what?
Sometimes, it feels that way.

25:32.415 --> 25:34.350
[ Sighs ]

25:34.384 --> 25:36.518
Thank you
for jumping behind the wheel.

25:36.553 --> 25:38.354
No problem.

25:38.388 --> 25:41.123
You log enough miles
between here and Sugar Land.

25:41.191 --> 25:43.192
[ Chuckles ]

25:43.226 --> 25:45.060
So, Garza's making some noise
about promoting me.

25:45.095 --> 25:48.631
Oh, look out, Beaumont.
Evan Parks is a high roller.

25:48.665 --> 25:50.866
[ Chuckles ] Well, he hasn't said anything
about a raise,

25:50.900 --> 25:52.368
but I'm not
letting up on him.

25:52.402 --> 25:54.536
Good for you.

25:54.571 --> 25:56.472
It's great.

25:56.539 --> 25:59.541
It's like we're both just
putting ourselves out there.

25:59.609 --> 26:02.344
What are you
talking about?

26:02.412 --> 26:05.147
Oh. Never mind.

26:07.484 --> 26:09.151
Cough it up, Parks.

26:09.185 --> 26:11.353
[ Chuckles ]
I just sort of...

26:11.388 --> 26:14.723
I ended up
going out on a date.

26:14.758 --> 26:16.659
Oh.

26:16.693 --> 26:20.496
Wow. That's, uh...

26:22.298 --> 26:23.866
I didn't know --
even know you were dating.

26:23.900 --> 26:26.869
I wasn't. I-I wasn't
even planning on it.

26:26.903 --> 26:29.405
It just sort of
felt like

26:29.439 --> 26:31.073
the universe was
pushing me out there, you know?

26:31.107 --> 26:32.608
Kind of like
what you're doing.

26:32.642 --> 26:35.411
Yeah.

26:35.445 --> 26:37.179
Yeah.

26:45.522 --> 26:47.289
[ Indistinct conversations ]

26:52.195 --> 26:54.496
My truck will be ready
in a day or two,

26:54.531 --> 26:56.298
so I think
I got it covered.

26:56.332 --> 26:58.500
Okay.
Great. I --

26:58.535 --> 27:00.669
[ cellphone ringing ]
Okay.

27:03.540 --> 27:05.941
[ Beep ]
Hey, Georgia.

27:05.975 --> 27:08.811
Georgia: Honey,
I made some calls,

27:08.878 --> 27:10.746
and I got an earful
about your mama's boyfriend.

27:10.780 --> 27:13.160
Garrett took donations
from the people in his church.

27:13.497 --> 27:16.656
For his non-profit. Skipped
town with the money.

27:19.622 --> 27:21.824
Are you kidding me?

27:21.858 --> 27:24.393
Nice job on Laughlin.

27:24.427 --> 27:25.928
We can talk about
that end-of-the-year bonus

27:25.962 --> 27:27.262
for coming in
under budget.

27:27.297 --> 27:30.499
That'd be great.
And the raise?

27:30.533 --> 27:34.436
Well, I got your promotion.
You're officially a foreman.

27:34.504 --> 27:36.772
And what about
the raise?

27:36.806 --> 27:39.775
I'm still fighting for that.
But I'm impressed, though.

27:39.809 --> 27:43.545
Wasn't sure this was gonna
work out for you.

27:43.613 --> 27:44.580
I got it.

27:50.720 --> 27:53.188
[ Birds chirping ]

27:54.958 --> 27:56.625
Riley: Mama,
it is killing me to have to

27:56.659 --> 27:58.594
tell you this about Garrett.
Now, come on outside.

27:58.661 --> 27:59.862
Oh, it is? 'Cause seems to me you're
just trying to find fault with him.

27:59.896 --> 28:02.631
Look, Georgia said
that he got people

28:02.665 --> 28:04.900
to donate to a foundation
to build another church.

28:04.968 --> 28:09.605
Oh, no. A good, selfless man
doing the work of the lord. Dear me.

28:09.639 --> 28:10.900
And then it was never built.
In Brazil?

28:10.925 --> 28:12.506
Maybe he's an international spy.

28:12.507 --> 28:13.433
Well, he's handsome enough.

28:13.458 --> 28:14.476
Okay. You know what?
You're not helping.

28:14.477 --> 28:16.712
And if he did half of what
you say, he'd be in jail.

28:16.780 --> 28:19.748
He was arrested. They couldn't
get him on anything.

28:19.783 --> 28:21.683
Wait. How long ago
did you say this happened?

28:21.718 --> 28:23.118
15 years ago in Laredo.

28:23.153 --> 28:25.120
I don't believe a word of it.
The Garrett I know

28:25.155 --> 28:27.156
gives his time and money
to the church.

28:27.190 --> 28:29.458
He doesn't take. He doesn't
even ask. I know the man.

28:29.526 --> 28:30.726
Yeah,
like I knew Kyle.

28:30.760 --> 28:32.027
Is that what this is about?
Yes, mama.

28:32.095 --> 28:33.462
That is exactly
what this is about.

28:33.496 --> 28:34.997
Why can't you
just be happy for me?

28:35.064 --> 28:37.399
All right.
Stop it, you two.

28:37.433 --> 28:38.801
Riley, Garrett hasn't given us any
reason to believe any of this is true.

28:38.835 --> 28:40.502
You're gonna take
her side right now?

28:40.537 --> 28:41.970
No, that is unbelievable.
I'm not taking si--

28:42.005 --> 28:43.972
you know what? I came
all the way down here

28:44.007 --> 28:45.741
because, mama,
I don't want you to get hurt.

28:45.775 --> 28:46.942
You know what hurts?

28:46.976 --> 28:48.677
The fact that my own daughter

28:48.711 --> 28:51.446
goes so far out of her way
to trounce on my dreams.

28:51.481 --> 28:54.917
Ugh. It wasn't that far
out of my way.

28:57.887 --> 29:01.056
You're on a time-out.

29:19.175 --> 29:22.110
So...still not gonna tell us
about him?

29:22.145 --> 29:24.546
Dee Ann, you're like a dog with a bone.
Kendra: What's the story?

29:24.614 --> 29:26.548
Is she seeing someone
or isn't she?

29:26.583 --> 29:28.917
We still don't know.
I'm not seeing -- I'm meeting.

29:28.952 --> 29:30.485
I'm meeting someone.

29:30.520 --> 29:32.454
Okay, so what
are you upset about?

29:32.488 --> 29:34.122
[ Voice breaking ] Look,
it's someone from my past...

29:34.157 --> 29:37.726
That not a day goes by
that I don't think about,

29:37.794 --> 29:40.762
and I'm...

29:40.797 --> 29:42.798
I'm just afraid
I'm gonna blow it, okay?

29:42.832 --> 29:44.666
But is there something
we can do to help?

29:44.701 --> 29:46.235
No. No. I'm fine.

29:48.071 --> 29:50.239
As long as I can figure out
what the hell to wear.

29:50.273 --> 29:52.007
Well, we're good at that,
right, girls?

29:52.075 --> 29:53.442
Here.
Why don't you wear this?

29:53.476 --> 29:54.776
Oh, I'd look
too young in that.

29:54.811 --> 29:56.011
You wouldn't
want that.

29:56.079 --> 29:58.413
How about this?
Dee Ann: Oh, yeah.

29:58.448 --> 30:01.750
And if you get cold,
uh...No.

30:01.784 --> 30:03.018
Selena has
a perfect wrap.

30:03.052 --> 30:04.086
Yeah, oh, that's great.
Yeah, okay.

30:04.120 --> 30:05.988
That's great.
That looks good.

30:06.022 --> 30:11.827
Here. You could use
a little good luck.

30:11.861 --> 30:13.228
Uh, no.
No, it's a spirit quartz.

30:13.263 --> 30:17.366
It radiates harmony.
It looks like a rock to me.

30:17.400 --> 30:20.035
Are you gonna let me help
or not?

30:20.069 --> 30:22.471
Yeah. Okay. I'll, uh --
I'll -- I'll take it with me.

30:22.505 --> 30:24.539
Now, what am I gonna wear
on the bottom?

30:24.574 --> 30:25.574
Ooh.

30:25.608 --> 30:26.608
This jean skirt.

30:26.643 --> 30:28.143
[ Sighing ] Okay.

30:28.177 --> 30:30.512
Now breathe.
I'm good. I'm good.

30:30.546 --> 30:31.947
You guys are great.
Thank you so much.

30:31.981 --> 30:33.649
Oh, of course.

30:33.683 --> 30:35.918
Let it out.
[ Sighs ] It's gonna be okay.

30:46.006 --> 30:47.974
[ Indistinct conversations ]

30:53.866 --> 30:55.432
[ Sighs ]

31:06.220 --> 31:07.654
Sam?

31:07.689 --> 31:10.557
Yeah.

31:10.591 --> 31:11.558
You're Jolene?

31:11.592 --> 31:13.193
I am.

31:13.227 --> 31:16.063
[ Laughs ] Hi.
Hi.

31:16.097 --> 31:17.965
Uh, go on.
Have a seat.

31:21.502 --> 31:23.770
I'm so happy
you showed up.

31:23.805 --> 31:25.472
I didn't know
if you would.

31:25.506 --> 31:27.107
And I would have understood
if you hadn't,

31:27.141 --> 31:28.775
you know, considering...

31:28.843 --> 31:31.178
[ Chuckling ] I'm just
talking too much, aren't I?

31:31.212 --> 31:34.181
No. It's -- it's okay.
I wanted to come.

31:34.215 --> 31:37.617
Good.

31:37.685 --> 31:39.653
Yeah?

31:39.687 --> 31:42.022
Nothing. I just --

31:42.056 --> 31:43.790
I wanted to say
your name out loud. I'm sorry.

31:43.825 --> 31:44.958
[ Both chuckle ]

31:46.561 --> 31:48.495
Just...feels weird.

31:48.529 --> 31:50.797
I know. [ Laughs ]
Me, too.

31:50.832 --> 31:52.299
I don't know
where to start.

31:52.333 --> 31:54.901
Ah! Maybe this.

31:54.936 --> 31:59.906
Uh, this is an old picture
from back in, uh...

31:59.974 --> 32:04.177
back in '92,
when he and I first met.

32:08.750 --> 32:10.717
[ Chuckles ]

32:10.785 --> 32:11.985
You look
just like him.

32:14.489 --> 32:15.956
You look
just like your daddy.

32:17.425 --> 32:20.827
Thank you.

32:23.765 --> 32:26.333
[ Chuckles ]

32:26.401 --> 32:28.735
[ Sighs ]

32:28.803 --> 32:31.004
[ Indistinct conversations ]

32:34.742 --> 32:38.712
Come on.
We're burning daylight.

32:38.746 --> 32:40.814
Thanks for giving me a ride.
Ah, no worries.

32:40.848 --> 32:43.517
Scratch my back...

32:43.584 --> 32:45.619
[ Chuckles ]

32:45.653 --> 32:48.321
Listen -- I was thinking
maybe you could, uh,

32:48.356 --> 32:49.723
set me up with Riley.

32:49.791 --> 32:52.359
You want me
to pimp out Riley?

32:52.393 --> 32:54.027
[ Scoffs ]
She's available.

32:55.863 --> 32:58.298
No, in fact,
she's seeing someone right now.

32:58.332 --> 32:59.433
[ Chuckles ]

32:59.467 --> 33:00.667
And I'll get
another ride.

33:00.701 --> 33:03.236
You've let her get away?
A fine piece of ass like that.

33:04.372 --> 33:06.573
Knock it off!

33:06.607 --> 33:09.276
You're fired, Parks!
Get him out of here now!

33:09.310 --> 33:10.210
Yeah,
I'm done with you, anyway!

33:16.851 --> 33:20.821
Jolene:
Hey. You okay?

33:20.888 --> 33:22.289
Yeah.
Just fighting with my mom.

33:22.323 --> 33:25.525
Didn't want to say anything about it.
You have enough on your plate.

33:25.560 --> 33:27.702
Oh, sweetie. I heard Georgia
checking up on her boyfriend.

33:27.727 --> 33:28.840
That's what this is about?

33:28.865 --> 33:30.605
Oh, it's always about
a man with my mama.

33:30.898 --> 33:32.766
She's gonna keep going ahead
no matter what.

33:32.800 --> 33:35.335
Well,
maybe he's okay.

33:35.369 --> 33:37.838
Maybe whatever he did,
he can put behind him.

33:37.872 --> 33:39.606
You know, we all have things
from our past

33:39.640 --> 33:40.540
we wish we could do over.

33:40.575 --> 33:42.542
Yeah. I hope so.

33:46.414 --> 33:47.814
How'd it go with Sam?

33:47.849 --> 33:48.982
[ Voice breaking ]
Amazing.

33:49.050 --> 33:52.486
It was...
just amazing.

33:52.520 --> 33:55.589
Are you okay?

33:55.623 --> 33:57.357
Riley,
Sam's m-my son.

33:57.391 --> 33:59.659
You're kidding me.

33:59.694 --> 34:01.862
And I was so nervous,
I had four cups of coffee,

34:01.896 --> 34:03.363
which didn't help.

34:03.431 --> 34:05.031
Oh, I wish
you would have seen him.

34:05.066 --> 34:06.967
No wonder you wanted to keep
all this to yourself.

34:07.001 --> 34:08.368
I didn't know
if he was gonna show.

34:08.402 --> 34:09.536
Well, he did.

34:09.603 --> 34:11.871
I never
wanted to give him up.

34:11.938 --> 34:14.174
I was just...
I was so young.

34:14.208 --> 34:15.809
I couldn't do it by myself,
you know? And...

34:15.842 --> 34:18.512
I kind of missed out
on his whole life.

34:18.545 --> 34:21.614
Hey. He's here now.
It's all gonna be okay.

34:21.649 --> 34:23.516
I was so happy
to see him.

34:23.583 --> 34:24.551
Oh!
[ Laughs ]

34:24.585 --> 34:25.886
Now I just...

34:25.920 --> 34:28.655
I feel kind of guilty and --
and excited

34:28.688 --> 34:30.657
and -- and l-like
I want to cry all the time,

34:30.690 --> 34:31.858
and my heart's gonna burst.

34:31.893 --> 34:33.426
And I worry about him,
you know?

34:33.460 --> 34:34.995
I just want to know where he is
and what he's doing

34:35.029 --> 34:37.330
and if he's okay.

34:37.364 --> 34:40.100
Why are you looking at me
like that?

34:40.134 --> 34:42.835
I just have never
really seen this in you before.

34:42.870 --> 34:44.437
It's really something.

34:44.472 --> 34:46.438
Like what?

34:46.474 --> 34:49.676
You just became a mom.

34:56.984 --> 35:01.821
[ Chuckles ]

35:01.856 --> 35:05.425
[ TV chatter ]

35:05.459 --> 35:08.995
Josh?

35:09.030 --> 35:10.897
Hey.
You here to see Jolene?

35:10.932 --> 35:12.699
Uh, no.
Actually, I, uh...

35:12.767 --> 35:13.833
I came to see you.

35:15.670 --> 35:17.337
W-would you mind?

35:19.640 --> 35:21.441
Hi.
[ Chuckles ]

35:21.475 --> 35:22.842
Um...

35:22.877 --> 35:24.911
This may sound
kind of strange.

35:24.946 --> 35:27.981
I just -- I just wanted us
to end on a good note.

35:28.015 --> 35:30.417
You're such a gentleman.

35:30.451 --> 35:33.453
No, I-I just think
you deserve an explanation.

35:33.487 --> 35:35.755
It's okay. I get it.

35:35.790 --> 35:38.625
My life is...
complicated right now

35:38.659 --> 35:42.562
and much more
than you bargained for.

35:42.597 --> 35:43.930
I was hoping maybe someday,
you know?

35:43.965 --> 35:45.832
Just not now.

35:45.866 --> 35:47.667
Well, at some point, maybe when
the stars align, you know?

35:47.702 --> 35:49.202
[ Both chuckle ]

35:49.270 --> 35:51.204
Neither one of us
is very good at this, are we?

35:56.110 --> 35:57.944
I'm an idiot.
I thought I'd come in here,

35:57.979 --> 35:59.980
"hello," "goodbye,"
nice to know you.

36:00.014 --> 36:01.648
Well,
we could still do that.

36:01.682 --> 36:04.317
[ Laughs ]

36:04.352 --> 36:07.587
It's just impossible...
right now for me and my life.

36:07.612 --> 36:09.885
Just that a picnic table and
that barbecue

36:10.091 --> 36:11.758
with a really great guy.

36:11.826 --> 36:13.226
[ Chuckles ]

36:15.696 --> 36:17.397
I get it.

36:20.301 --> 36:23.737
It was really great
getting to know you.

36:23.804 --> 36:28.908
Yeah.

36:34.982 --> 36:36.783
[ Door opens, closes ]

36:41.822 --> 36:43.556
You are so beautiful,
Linny.

36:43.591 --> 36:47.260
I think
my heart skipped a beat.

36:47.295 --> 36:50.397
And I've got us a reservation
at Galatoire's for tonight.

36:50.431 --> 36:53.733
[ Gasps ] French creole!
Yeah.

36:53.768 --> 36:56.970
Oh,
that was just a hunch.

36:57.004 --> 37:00.140
I might show you off
just a little bit.

37:00.207 --> 37:01.875
Oh, you.

37:01.942 --> 37:04.210
You know, I've got
an old business partner in town,

37:04.245 --> 37:06.846
and I thought
we'd meet him for drinks.

37:06.914 --> 37:09.649
Business partner?
You sell cars.

37:09.717 --> 37:11.318
Well,
that's fine for the wallet,

37:11.385 --> 37:12.952
but it does nothing
for the soul.

37:12.987 --> 37:16.089
Um, I'm not sure
I follow you.

37:16.157 --> 37:17.724
Well, see,
he and I are talking about

37:17.758 --> 37:19.259
building a little church

37:19.327 --> 37:21.928
in his hometown
outside of Sao Paulo.

37:21.962 --> 37:24.364
Sao Paulo...
Brazil?

37:24.398 --> 37:25.865
Brazil. Yeah.

37:25.900 --> 37:28.001
Oh. Yeah, I mean,
it's very poor there.

37:28.035 --> 37:30.704
And the church would do them
a world of good, so...

37:30.738 --> 37:33.484
And, you know, if we get a few
converts from the catholics,

37:33.509 --> 37:35.509
that wouldn't hurt either,
would it?

37:37.445 --> 37:41.781
So, you're --
you're building a new church.

37:41.816 --> 37:45.418
What do you call it?
A sister church.

37:45.486 --> 37:48.121
A sister church?
Mm-hmm.

37:48.189 --> 37:49.989
Right.

37:50.024 --> 37:52.125
You know, maybe we could
talk to some of your friends,

37:52.150 --> 37:54.150
see if they want to get in on it, too.

37:54.228 --> 37:56.963
You know, you seem to know
everybody who's anybody in this town.

37:56.997 --> 37:59.132
[ Inhales deeply ] Garrett.
Hmm?

37:59.166 --> 38:01.835
[ Sniffles ]
This is what's gonna happen.

38:01.869 --> 38:06.039
You're going to open your trunk
and hand me my suitcase.

38:06.073 --> 38:08.641
I'm going to go
back inside.

38:08.676 --> 38:11.010
You're going to get in your car,
and you're gonna leave.

38:12.947 --> 38:15.048
Linette,
what has gotten into you?

38:15.082 --> 38:16.383
Laredo.

38:19.120 --> 38:23.890
Okay. Hang on, now.
'Cause that -- that, um...

38:23.958 --> 38:26.493
that was a misunderstanding.
And I can explain that.

38:26.527 --> 38:27.761
I don't want to hear it.

38:27.828 --> 38:29.629
[ Sighs ]

38:29.663 --> 38:31.965
I always thought
you were too good to be true.

38:31.999 --> 38:35.034
Honey, you're making
a terrible mistake.

38:36.937 --> 38:39.406
I've made
so many mistakes.

38:39.440 --> 38:41.441
Thank God you're not
gonna be one of them.

38:48.949 --> 38:51.751
[ Crickets chirping ]

38:55.689 --> 38:57.395
I'm so sorry.

38:58.402 --> 39:00.402
I'm such a fool.

39:01.028 --> 39:08.635
Mama, you are
the farthest thing from it.

39:08.669 --> 39:10.003
When your daddy died,

39:10.037 --> 39:13.106
I swear I lost
the ground beneath me.

39:13.174 --> 39:15.909
I lost my balance,
and I just never got it back.

39:15.976 --> 39:17.410
Yes, you have.

39:17.445 --> 39:18.878
My feet on the ground?
No.

39:18.913 --> 39:22.515
Mama, you just said,
"when daddy died."

39:22.583 --> 39:24.050
You know that's the first time
in all these years

39:24.084 --> 39:26.653
that you didn't say
he left us or abandoned us?

39:26.687 --> 39:27.821
I sure do.

39:27.888 --> 39:29.489
That's right.

39:29.523 --> 39:30.924
You actually really said
what happened.

39:30.991 --> 39:32.525
That's a start.

39:32.560 --> 39:36.029
[ Sighs ]

39:36.063 --> 39:38.798
You and me,
we're tough as squirrel meat

39:38.833 --> 39:39.999
and twice as pretty.

39:40.067 --> 39:42.669
Only twice? Lord.

39:42.703 --> 39:44.103
[ Both laugh ]

39:44.138 --> 39:45.772
I think you're trying to say
we're gonna be just fine.

39:45.806 --> 39:47.807
With or without a man.
And what about you, honey?

39:47.842 --> 39:49.843
Are you putting yourself
out there yet?

39:49.877 --> 39:52.579
I thought about it.
Took a run at it.

39:52.613 --> 39:54.013
Had a date?
Yeah.

39:54.048 --> 39:55.849
Yeah.
[ Chuckles ]

39:55.916 --> 39:57.517
It started off good.

39:57.551 --> 40:00.587
Made me realize I need to
just focus on the kids.

40:00.654 --> 40:04.090
[ Sighs ]

40:04.124 --> 40:06.092
Well, I learned from the best.
[ Knock on door ]

40:09.196 --> 40:11.297
Be right back. Okay.
Okay.

40:13.634 --> 40:15.101
Lacey:
Oh, thanks for calling.

40:15.135 --> 40:16.803
I didn't feel like
staying home by myself

40:16.837 --> 40:18.037
while Dale's out
with his buddies.

40:18.105 --> 40:22.175
Did you talk to him?

40:22.209 --> 40:23.610
He promised me,
Riley.

40:23.644 --> 40:25.078
On our second date,
Dale said,

40:25.145 --> 40:26.379
"Lace, you know
we're gonna get married one day

40:26.413 --> 40:27.780
and have a million babies,
don't you?"

40:27.815 --> 40:29.182
And I believed him.

40:29.216 --> 40:31.484
Okay,
but going off the pill?

40:31.519 --> 40:33.386
Sharlyn Ramsey did it,
and her husband came around.

40:33.420 --> 40:35.889
Yeah, but you're better than that.
I mean, you can't lie to someone you love

40:35.923 --> 40:48.601
without it eventually tearing
the relationship apart.

40:48.636 --> 40:50.103
I'm gonna go
check on the kids.

40:50.170 --> 40:51.371
Okay.
You get some pizza.

40:51.405 --> 40:52.739
We'll make a night of it,
okay?

40:52.773 --> 40:53.506
Okay.
Okay.

40:59.947 --> 41:03.216
[ Sighs ]

41:06.787 --> 41:12.492
Cookie.

41:12.526 --> 41:13.860
Linette:
Lacey. What's going on?

41:16.430 --> 41:17.797
You look like
you saw a ghost.

41:17.831 --> 41:19.465
Riley: Hey.

41:19.500 --> 41:20.700
Let's thaw some pizza
and have a drink.

41:23.871 --> 41:26.005
Mama,
is that the second bottle?

41:26.073 --> 41:27.307
Linette: Third.

41:27.341 --> 41:28.708
[ Laughs ]

41:28.742 --> 41:30.777
But I've been eating,
munching along the way.

41:30.811 --> 41:32.045
[ Laughs ]

41:34.733 --> 41:38.733
